cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper is about automating cluster management, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of a relational database and SQL queries also suggests a connection to database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a declarative approach to cluster management, which involves optimization objectives and constraints, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the challenges of adding new features to existing systems, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a tool called Weave, which involves synthesizing an encoding of queries into an optimization model, suggesting a connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
